This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `adjustResize` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI defaults to **edge-to-edge** rendering, so the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer drives layout changes. You need to react to **window insets** instead.

### Recommended fix — handle IME insets on Android

**1. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`**, listen for keyboard insets and apply bottom padding:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Android.OS.Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Edge-to-edge is now the default; react to the keyboard inset
        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Remove the old platform-specific call** if you have one:

```diff
- App.Current.On<Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.Android>()
-     .UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize);
```

**3. Keep `adjustResize` in your manifest** (it's deprecated but still needed as a hint for the compat insets listener):

```xml
<!-- Platforms/Android/AndroidManifest.xml -->
<activity ... android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" />
```

### Why this works

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (edge-to-edge) |
|---|---|
| OS resized the window for you | App draws behind keyboard & nav bar |
| `adjustResize` triggered layout | Insets tell you *where* system UI is |

The `WindowInsetsCompat` listener fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes. Setting bottom padding on the root view pushes your input bar up — exactly like the old resize behavior.

### iOS

iOS `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` still works in MAUI on .NET 10, so no changes are needed there. If you disabled it, re-enable with:

```csharp
#if IOS
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(h =>
    Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect = true);
#endif
```
